dan.</p><p>41:32 – <strong>Susan McCarthy </strong>—&nbsp;Joanna Handlin Smith,<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Art-Doing-Good-Charity-China/dp/0520253639/ref=sr_1_3?crid=37L6TPT0W2WMB&amp;keywords=The+Art+of+Doing+Good&amp;qid=1680724807&amp;s=books&amp;sprefix=the+art+of+doing+good%2Cstripbooks%2C116&amp;sr=1-3&amp;ufe=app_do%3Aamzn1.fos.18ed3cb5-28d5-4975-8bc7-93deae8f9840" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"> <em>The Art of Doing Good: Charity in Late Ming China</em></a></p><p>49:18 – <strong>Brian DeMare </strong>— William Hinton, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Fanshen-Documentary-Revolution-Chinese-Village/dp/1583671757/ref=sr_1_1?crid=269UQM44P1MHK&amp;keywords=William+Hinton+Fanshen&amp;qid=1680725058&amp;s=books&amp;sprefix=william+hinton+fanshen%2Cstripbooks%2C99&amp;sr=1-1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>Fanshen</em></a></p><p>50:47 – <strong>Juliet Lu</strong> — Maria Repnikova, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Chinese-Power-Elements-Global-China/dp/1108792685/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2T0TT4JSOS803&amp;keywords=Maria+Repnikova&amp;qid=1680725189&amp;s=books&amp;sprefix=maria+repnikova%2Cstripbooks%2C99&amp;sr=1-1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>Chinese Soft Power</em></a>, and Samuel L. Jackson reading Adam Mansbach's <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Go-F-k-to-Sleep-audiobook/dp/B0055QAEVE/ref=sr_1_1?keywords=go+the+fck+to+sleep+book&amp;qid=1680725275&amp;s=books&amp;sprefix=Go+the+F%2Cstripbooks%2C109&amp;sr=1-1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>Go the F--k to Sleep</em></a><strong> </strong></p><p>58:29 – <strong>Sabina Knight </strong>— Wu Ming-Yi, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Man-Compound-Eyes-Novel/dp/B097RZK3J7/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1941BX7UUWDQH&amp;keywords=The+Man+with+the+Compound+Eyes&amp;qid=1680725378&amp;s=audible&amp;sprefix=the+man+with+the+compound+eyes%2Caudible%2C108&amp;sr=1-1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>The Man with the Compound Eyes</em></a>, translated by Darryl Sterk</p><p><a 