        <![CDATA[<p>We proudly present Episode 1 of the new season of&nbsp;<em>Strangers in China,&nbsp;</em>part of the Sinica Network from The China Project. In this season, host Clay Baldo provides an intimate look at the lockdown in Shanghai, from the foreboding that preceded it through the harrowing days of the lockdown itself.</p><p>Be sure to subscribe to the show, too! Just look up Strangers in China in your podcast app of choice and hit subscribe.</p><p>2:21 –&nbsp;A preview of this season of Strangers in China</p><p>8:23 – The Shanghai fāngcāng方舱 and emergence of spontaneous mass gatherings</p><p>13:28 – Explaining the role of neighborhood committees/ jūwěihuì 居委会 in China&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>18:39 – The exploration of mental health throughout this podcast</p><p>24:21 – Clay’s process in producing the podcast</p><p>28:06 – The editorial choice to not dub over Chinese speakers&nbsp;</p><p>31:29 – Can the protests like the one that broke out on Urumqi Lu emerge again?</p><p>37:15 – Examples of strong group solidarity during the lockdown</p><p>43:35 – Clay’s thoughts on the recent loosening of restrictions</p><p><a href="https://thechinaproject.com/2023/01/05/clay-baldo-is-no-stranger-to-china/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">A transcript of this podcast is available at TheChinaProject.com</a>.</p><p><strong>Recommendations:</strong></p><p><strong>Clay</strong>: 3 Shanghai fashion Instagram accounts to follow – Windowsen (@windowsen), Susu, (@_su.su.su.su). Lexi (@jing_sen_); and the book <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Seeing-like-State-Certain-Condition/dp/0300078153/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2R33F0HH7Z933&amp;keywords=Seeing+like+a+state&amp;qid=1672941264&amp;qu=eyJxc2MiOiIxLjkyIiwicXNhIjoiMS43MiIsInFzcCI6IjEuODYifQ%3D%3D&amp;sprefix=seeing+like+a+state%2Caps%2C147&amp;sr=8-1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>Seeing Like a State</em></a> by James C. Scott.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Kaiser</strong>: <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Long-Ships-Review-Books-Classics/dp/1590173465/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1EYX558HZNMFU&amp;keywords=the+long+ships+frans+g.+bengtsson&amp;qid=1672941360&amp;qu=eyJxc2MiOiIyLjEwIiwicXNhIjoiMS42NyIsInFzcCI6IjEuODQifQ%3D%3D&amp;sprefix=The+Long+Ships%2Caps%2C136&amp;sr=8-1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>The Long Ships</em></a><em> </em>by Frans Bengtsson</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>See Privacy Policy at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy</a> and California Privacy Notice at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info</a>.</p>]]>
