      <itunes:title>The investigative team from MIT Technology Review that found major flaws with the DoJ's China Initiative</itunes:title>
      <itunes:episodeType>full</itunes:episodeType>
      <itunes:summary>This week on the Sinica Podcast, Kaiser chats with Eileen Guo and Jess Aloe, two members of the three-person team of reporters at the MIT Technology Review who took a data-centered look at the U.S. Department of Justice's China Initiative and uncovered serious problems: an ill-defined mission, low conviction rates, post hoc efforts to remove cases previously described as falling under the China Initiative, and strong evidence of racial profiling.

