        <![CDATA[<p>This week on Sinica, Kaiser and Jeremy welcome Lizzi Lee (李其 Lǐ Qi), SupChina contributor and host of the excellent Chinese-language YouTube channel Wall Street Today, and Jude Blanchette, Freeman Chair at the Center for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS), to talk about the spate of regulatory actions, new rules, and Party-led initiatives that, taken together, we at SupChina have started calling the “Red New Deal.” Can these be understood as different facets of a larger, overarching program to remake China’s economy and society? Or are they better understood as distinct moves by different bureaucracies within the Party-state that happen to coincide in time? Listen in as we try to sort through what it all means.</p><p><br></p><p>11:42 - Lizzi’s contrarian take on whether the new regulation adds up to something bigger</p><p><br></p><p>15:00 - The logic of the political calendar in China</p><p><br></p><p>22:56 - What did the response to the Li Guangman viral post mean?</p><p><br></p><p>33:14 - Kevin Rudd’s take on what it all means – the “red thread”</p><p><br></p><p>43:32 - No, this isn’t the Cultural Revolution</p><p><br></p><p>53:00 - Is this a return to true communism?</p><p><br></p><p>57:34 - Is Xi Jinping China’s biggest tiger mom?</p><p><br></p><p><a href="https://supchina.com/2021/09/16/red-new-deal-or-raw-new-deal-unraveling-chinas-astonishing-barrage-of-regulatory-action/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">A transcript of this interview is available on SupChina.com.</a></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Recommendations</strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Jeremy: </strong><a href="https://supchina.com/podcast/eat-the-buddha-a-conversation-with-award-winning-author-barbara-demick/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">NüVoices Podcast</a>: Barabara Demick on <em>Eat the Buddha</em>, the final NüVoices episode on SupChina; and the Vice video on YouTube, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hYVepff7ucA" rel="noopener 