      <title>China, Russia, and the U.S.: Does the 'strategic triangle' still matter?</title>
      <description>
        <![CDATA[<p>Have China and Russia entered into a de facto anti-American alliance? Is Russia, which in Soviet days was for a time the “older brother” to Mao’s China, now comfortable with playing junior partner to Xi’s China? And has the United States, which in its opening to China demonstrated formidable acuity in managing the “strategic triangle,” now jettisoned that model and its logic? This week on Sinica, Kaiser is joined by <a href="https://www.eurasiagroup.net/people/awyne" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Ali Wyne</a>, a senior analyst with Eurasia Group's Global Macro practice, to discuss the motivations, the capabilities, and the strategies of Beijing and Moscow in their dealings with Washington — and with each other.</p><p>3:54: What of the rules-based international order?</p><p>15:04: The relationship between China and Russia</p><p>27:35: Inflection points in the early 2000s</p><p>48:52: Strategies and tactics employed by China and Russia&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Recommendations:</strong></p><p><strong>Ali:</strong> <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Stronger-Adapting-Americas-Competitive-Interdependence/dp/0300251254" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>Stronger: Adapting America's China Strategy in an Age of Competitive Interdependence</em></a>, by Ryan Hass, and the documentary series <a href="https://www.cnn.com/shows/chasing-life" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>Chasing Life</em></a>, by Sanjay Gupta.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Kaiser:</strong> The audiobook for <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Committed-Viet-Thanh-Nguyen/dp/0802157068" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>The Committed</em></a>, written by Viet Thanh Nguyen and narrated by Francois Chau. </p><p>See Privacy Policy at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy</a> and California Privacy Notice at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info</a>.</p>]]>
