      <title>Southeast Asia in the dragon's shadow: A conversation with Sebastian Strangio</title>
      <description>
        <![CDATA[<p>This week on Sinica, Kaiser and Jeremy chat with Sebastian Strangio, the Southeast Asia editor at The Diplomat, about his new book, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Dragons-Shadow-Southeast-Chinese-Century/dp/0300234031" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>In the Dragon's Shadow: Southeast Asia in the Chinese Century</em></a>. The book examines how each of the members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (except Brunei) has coped with China's rapid reemergence as a regional superpower, and offers superbly written on-the-ground reportage by a longtime resident of the region.</p><p><strong>Recommendations:</strong></p><p><strong>Jeremy:</strong> The novel <a href="https://www.amazon.com/True-Grit-Novel-Charles-Portis/dp/159020459X" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>True Grit</em></a>, by Charles Portis.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Sebastian:</strong> The novel <a href="https://www.amazon.com/World-Yesterday-Stefan-Zweig/dp/0803226616" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><em>World of Yesterday</em></a>, by Austrian writer Stefan Zweig.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Kaiser:</strong> The Swedish progressive metal supergroup <a href="https://soenmusic.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Soen</a>. Start with the album <em>Lykaia</em>.</p><p>See Privacy Policy at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy</a> and California Privacy Notice at <a href="https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">https://art19.com/privacy#do-not-sell-my-info</a>.</p>]]>
